results.name: Largest number m such that n^m divides tau(n), where tau(n)=A000594(n) is Ramanujan's tau function.
link: Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, Tau Function.
mathematica: f[n_] := Block[{m = 0}, While[Mod[RamanujanTau@n, n^m] == 0, m++]; m - 1]; Array[f, 93, 2] (* _Robert G. Wilson v_, Dec 23 2017 *)
results.author: _Seiichi Manyama_, Dec 22 2017
